<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="1103" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1103">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/20495½</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Funston</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Adjutant General of the Army</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Fort Sam Houston</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-06">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>4509. Following received from General Pershing from Columbus dated
                            February 5: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>Expeditionary forces returning from Mexico crossed the line
                                    to-day, last troops leaving Mexico at 3 p.m. Transportation
                                    pertaining to expedition was sufficient to bring out all
                                    Government property. Am leaving to-morrow Roon for El Paso.
                                    General Swift will supervise movement of remaining troops
                                    ordered to new stations.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>As soon as General Swift has completed duty referred to he will proceed
                            to El Paso to command cavalry division.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Funston</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>